By the addition formula for tangent, \[\tan (\alpha + \beta + \gamma) = \frac{\tan \alpha + \tan \beta + \tan \gamma - \tan \alpha \tan \beta \tan \gamma}{1 - (\tan \alpha \tan \beta + \tan \beta \tan \gamma + \tan \gamma \tan \alpha)},\]so \[\infty = \frac{\frac{a}{c} + \frac{b}{c} + \frac{a + b}{c} - \frac{a}{c} \cdot \frac{b}{c} \cdot \frac{a + b}{c}}{1 - \left( \frac{a}{c} \cdot \frac{b}{c} + \frac{b}{c} \cdot \frac{a + b}{c} + \frac{a + b}{c} \cdot \frac{a}{c} \right)}.\]This simplifies to \[\frac{a}{c} \cdot \frac{b}{c} \cdot \frac{a + b}{c} = 1.\]Since $HF = 6$ and $HC = 15$, $CF = 21$.
